# Employment Trends Across Town Sizes

A boxplot was used to visually compare employment rates across various town sizes. Figure 1 @fig-boxplot provides a clear overview of how employment outcomes vary by the size of the town. Small towns show a wider spread but the highest median employment rates, while cities exhibit the lowest employment rates with less variation.



::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output-display}
